org.apache.poi.ss.util

Class SheetBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.ss.util.SheetBuilder

  • public class SheetBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    Class SheetBuilder provides an easy way of building workbook sheets from 2D array of Objects. It can be used in test cases to improve code readability or in Swing applications with tables.(Class SheetBuilder提供了一种从2D对象数组构建工作簿工作表的简单方法。它可以在测试用例中使用以提高代码可读性或在带有表的Swing应用程序中使用。)
    Author:
    Roman Kashitsyn

      • build

        public Sheet build()
        Builds sheet from parent workbook and 2D array with cell values. Creates rows anyway (even if row contains only null cells), creates cells if either corresponding array value is not null or createEmptyCells property is true. The conversion is performed in the following way:

        • Numbers become numeric cells.
        • java.util.Date or java.util.Calendar instances become date cells.
        • String with leading '=' char become formulas (leading '=' will be truncated).
        • Other objects become strings via Object.toString() method call.
        (从父工作簿和带有单元格值的2D数组生成工作表。无论如何都会创建行（即使行仅包含空单元格），如果相应的数组值不为空或SEARCH EmptyCells属性为真，则创建单元格。转换以以下方式执行：数字变成数字单元格。java.util.Date或java.util.Calendar实例变成日期单元格。以“=”开头的字符串成为公式（以“=”开头的字符串将被截断）。其他对象通过Target.toString（）方法调用变成字符串。)
        Returns:
        newly created sheet(新创建的工作表)
